### [Psalms Chapter 103](../../../bib/kjv/psa103.htm#001.md)

[Psalms 103:1](../../../bib/kjv/psa103.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_001">psa 103:1</span></span>

A Psalm of joyous praise, in which the writer rises from a thankful
acknowledgment of personal blessings to a lively celebration of God's
gracious attributes, as not only intrinsically worthy of praise, but as
specially suited to man's frailty. He concludes by invoking all
creatures to unite in his song. (Psa. 103:1-22)

Bless, &c.--when God is the object, praise.

my soul--myself ([Psa 3:3](../../../bib/kjv/psa003.htm#003.md); [Psa
25:1](../../../bib/kjv/psa025.htm#001).md), with allusion to the act, as
one of intelligence.

all . . . within me-- ([Deu 6:5](../../../bib/kjv/deu006.htm#005).md).

his holy name-- ([Psa 5:11](../../../bib/kjv/psa005.htm#011).md), His
complete moral perfections.

[Psalms 103:2](../../../bib/kjv/psa103.htm#002.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_002">psa 103:2</span></span>

forget not all--not any, none of His benefits.

[Psalms 103:3](../../../bib/kjv/psa103.htm#003.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_003">psa 103:3</span></span>

diseases--as penal inflictions ([Deu
29:22](../../../bib/kjv/deu029.htm#022.md); [Ch2
21:19](../../../bib/kjv/ch2021.htm#019).md).

[Psalms 103:4](../../../bib/kjv/psa103.htm#004.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_004">psa 103:4</span></span>

redeemeth--Cost is implied.

destruction--literally, "pit of corruption" ([Psa
16:10](../../../bib/kjv/psa016.htm#010).md).

crowneth--or, "adorneth" ([Psa 65:11](../../../bib/kjv/psa065.htm#011).md).

tender mercies--compassions (compare [Psa
25:6](../../../bib/kjv/psa025.htm#006.md); [Psa
40:11](../../../bib/kjv/psa040.htm#011).md).

[Psalms 103:5](../../../bib/kjv/psa103.htm#005.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_005">psa 103:5</span></span>

By God's provision, the saint retains a youthful vigor like the eagles
([Psa 92:14](../../../bib/kjv/psa092.htm#014.md); compare [Isa
40:31](../../../bib/kjv/isa040.htm#031).md).

[Psalms 103:6](../../../bib/kjv/psa103.htm#006.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_006">psa 103:6</span></span>

Literally, "righteousness and judgments," denoting various acts of God's
government.

[Psalms 103:7](../../../bib/kjv/psa103.htm#007.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_007">psa 103:7</span></span>

ways--of providence, &c., as usual ([Psa
25:4](../../../bib/kjv/psa025.htm#004.md); [Psa
67:2](../../../bib/kjv/psa067.htm#002).md).

acts--literally, "wonders" ([Psa 7:11](../../../bib/kjv/psa007.htm#011.md);
[Psa 78:17](../../../bib/kjv/psa078.htm#017).md).

[Psalms 103:8](../../../bib/kjv/psa103.htm#008.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_008">psa 103:8</span></span>

God's benevolence implies no merit. He shows it to sinners, who also are
chastened for a time ([Exo 34:6](../../../bib/kjv/exo034.htm#006).md).

keep (anger)--in [Lev 19:18](../../../bib/kjv/lev019.htm#018.md), bear a
grudge ([Jer 3:5](../../../bib/kjv/jer003.htm#005.md), [Jer
3:12](../../../bib/kjv/jer003.htm#012).md).

[Psalms 103:11](../../../bib/kjv/psa103.htm#011.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_011">psa 103:11</span></span>

great--efficient.

[Psalms 103:12](../../../bib/kjv/psa103.htm#012.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_012">psa 103:12</span></span>

removed . . . from us--so as no longer to affect our relations to Him.

[Psalms 103:13](../../../bib/kjv/psa103.htm#013.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_013">psa 103:13</span></span>

pitieth--literally, "has compassion on."

[Psalms 103:14](../../../bib/kjv/psa103.htm#014.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_014">psa 103:14</span></span>

he--"who formed," [Psa 94:9](../../../bib/kjv/psa094.htm#009.md).

knoweth our frame--literally, "our form."

we are dust--made of and tending to it ([Gen
2:7](../../../bib/kjv/gen002.htm#007).md).

[Psalms 103:15](../../../bib/kjv/psa103.htm#015.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_015">psa 103:15</span></span>

So short and frail is life that a breath may destroy it.

it is gone--literally, "it is not."

know it no more--no more recognize him ([Psa
90:6](../../../bib/kjv/psa090.htm#006.md); [Isa
40:6-8](../../../bib/kjv/isa040.htm#006).md).

[Psalms 103:17](../../../bib/kjv/psa103.htm#017.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_017">psa 103:17</span></span>

For similar contrast compare [Psa
90:2-6](../../../bib/kjv/psa090.htm#002.md); [Psa
102:27-28](../../../bib/kjv/psa102.htm#027.md).

[Psalms 103:18](../../../bib/kjv/psa103.htm#018.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_018">psa 103:18</span></span>

such . . . covenant--limits the general terms preceding.

righteousness--as usual ([Psa 7:17](../../../bib/kjv/psa007.htm#017.md);
[Psa 31:1](../../../bib/kjv/psa031.htm#001).md).

[Psalms 103:19](../../../bib/kjv/psa103.htm#019.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_019">psa 103:19</span></span>

God's firm and universal dominion is a pledge that He will keep His
promises ([Psa 11:4](../../../bib/kjv/psa011.htm#004.md); [Psa
47:8](../../../bib/kjv/psa047.htm#008).md).

[Psalms 103:20](../../../bib/kjv/psa103.htm#020.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_020">psa 103:20</span></span>

do his commandments . . . word--or, literally, "so as to hearken," &c.,
that is, their acts of obedience are prompt, so that they are ever ready
to hear, and know, and follow implicitly His declared will (compare [Deu
26:17](../../../bib/kjv/deu026.htm#017.md); [Luk
1:19](../../../bib/kjv/luk001.htm#019).md).

[Psalms 103:21](../../../bib/kjv/psa103.htm#021.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_021">psa 103:21</span></span>

ye his hosts--myriads, or armies, as corresponding to angels of great
power \[[Psa 103:20](../../../bib/kjv/psa103.htm#020.md)\], denoting
multitudes also.

[Psalms 103:22](../../../bib/kjv/psa103.htm#022.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_022">psa 103:22</span></span>

all his works--creatures of every sort, everywhere.

